A student was left feeling sick when she opened a box of doughnuts delivered by Domino’s Pizza and found them covered in mould.

Chloe Smith, 20, and a friend ordered a pizza and the sweet treats - a recent addition to the chain’s menu - from a branch in Teddington, south-west London, following a late night study session.

But they opened the doughnut box and were hit by a stench, with all four covered in black mould. Now Miss Smith has insisted she will not be buying from Domino’s again after the nasty surprise.

