A Domino’s spokesman said the matter was being taken ‘extremely seriously’.

She said: ‘Food quality is of utmost priority for Domino’s and we have strict processes and procedures in place for handling all ingredients and products.

‘We have asked that the customer contact us immediately in order for us to conduct a full and thorough investigation into this issue.’

Miss Smith has complained to Richmond upon Thames London Borough Council and environmental health officers are now investigating.

